sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Endpoint
    participant Mediator
    participant Validator
    participant Handler
    participant Domain as GameSession
    participant CodeGen as SessionCodeGenerator
    participant DB as Database
    participant Events
    participant SSE as SSE Service

    Client->>Endpoint: POST /api/v1/tracking/sessions
    Note right of Client: {gameId, sessionType, participants[]}

    Endpoint->>Endpoint: Extract payload
    Endpoint->>Endpoint: Create CreateSessionCommand

    Endpoint->>Mediator: Send(command)

    Mediator->>Validator: Validate(command)
    Validator->>Validator: Check gameId is valid
    Validator->>Validator: Check sessionType is valid enum
    Validator->>Validator: Verify at least 1 participant
    Validator->>DB: Verify game exists
    DB-->>Validator: Game found ✓
    Validator->>Mediator: Validation passed ✓

    Mediator->>Handler: Handle(command)

    Handler->>CodeGen: GenerateSessionCode()
    CodeGen->>CodeGen: Generate 6-char random code
    CodeGen->>DB: Check uniqueness
    DB-->>CodeGen: Code unique ✓
    CodeGen-->>Handler: SessionCode = "ABC123"

    Handler->>Domain: GameSession.Create(userId, gameId, sessionType, code)
    Domain->>Domain: Status = Active
    Domain->>Domain: CreatedAt = UtcNow
    Domain->>Domain: SessionCode = code

    loop For each participant
        Handler->>Domain: session.AddParticipant(participantInfo)
        Domain->>Domain: Add to Participants collection
    end

    Domain->>Events: Raise SessionCreatedEvent

    Handler->>DB: SaveAsync(session)
    DB-->>Handler: Session saved ✓

    Handler->>SSE: CreateStreamChannel(sessionId)
    SSE-->>Handler: Channel ready ✓

    Handler->>Events: Publish SessionCreatedEvent

    Handler-->>Mediator: SessionDto
    Mediator-->>Endpoint: SessionDto

    Endpoint-->>Client: 201 Created
    Note left of Client: {sessionId, sessionCode, sseStreamUrl}
